35-year-old hairdresser, Anita Samuel, was yesterday brought before an Ikeja Chief Magistrates’ Court, Lagos, on a charge of assault. She was accused of stabbing her friend for not allowing her to taste the gari, which was eating. Gari is made from cassava Samuel pleaded not guilty. Prosecuting Assistant Superintendent of Police (ASP) Akeem Raji alleged that the defendant stabbed Miss Ediomo Linus with a broken bottle on the forehead, following their gari disagreement Raji said the defendant told the complainant to let her taste the gari but she refused. “The following day, the complainant greeted the defendant, but she did not answer. “This led to an argument, which made the defendant to lock the door and hit her with a broken bottle on the head,” he said. Chief Magistrate Oyeladun Layinka granted the defendant N200, 000 bail with two sureties in the like sum. She said the sureties must be employed with evidence of two years tax payment to the Lagos State Government. The case has continues on April 25.